# Which APIs Actually Use Real Google Search? (2026)

## TL;DR: For Most Recent Forums & Research

**üèÜ Winner: Perplexity API**

**Why**: Real-time index (200B URLs), constantly refreshed, `latest_updated` filter, 400ms speed

---

## The Truth About Search APIs

### APIs That Use **ACTUAL Google SERP**

| API | How It Works | Recency | Cost |
|-----|--------------|---------|------|
| **Serper** | Scrapes Google SERP in real-time | ‚úÖ Real-time Google | $50/month (50k queries) |
| **SerpApi** | Scrapes Google SERP in real-time | ‚úÖ Real-time Google | $75/month (5k searches) |
| **ValueSERP** | Scrapes Google SERP in real-time | ‚úÖ Real-time Google | $50/month (10k searches) |

### APIs With **Own Index** (NOT Google)

| API | How It Works | Recency | Cost |
|-----|--------------|---------|------|
| **Perplexity API** | Own index (200B URLs), constantly refreshed | ‚úÖ Real-time (seconds) | $5 per 1k requests |
| **Tavily** | Own crawler + real-time search | ‚úÖ Real-time | $0.008/credit |
| **Exa AI** | Own neural index | ‚ö†Ô∏è Less recent | Enterprise |

### ‚ö†Ô∏è SERPGRID Warning

