## MCP Integration for Roo Code

### Perplexity MCP Server

**Available**: [MCP Cursor - Perplexity](https://mcpcursor.com/server/perplexity-1-mcp)

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "perplexity": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-perplexity"],
      "env": {
        "PERPLEXITY_API_KEY": "${PERPLEXITY_API_KEY}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Serper MCP Server (DIY)

Create `~/.claude/serper-mcp-server.js`:

```javascript
#!/usr/bin/env node
import { McpServer } from '@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/mcp.js';
import { StdioServerTransport } from '@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/stdio.js';
import { z } from 'zod';

const SERPER_API_KEY = process.env.SERPER_API_KEY;

const server = new McpServer({ name: 'serper', version: '1.0.0' });

server.tool('google_search', 'Search Google SERP in real-time', {
  query: z.string(),
  num: z.number().default(10),
  time_filter: z.enum(['h', 'd', 'w', 'm', 'y']).optional()
}, async ({ query, num, time_filter }) => {
  const tbs = time_filter ? `qdr:${time_filter}` : undefined;

  const response = await fetch('https://google.serper.dev/search', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
      'X-API-KEY': SERPER_API_KEY,
      'Content-Type': 'application/json'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({ q: query, num, tbs })
  });

  const data = await response.json();
  return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify(data, null, 2) }] };
});

const transport = new StdioServerTransport();
await server.connect(transport);
```

Add to Roo Code:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "serper": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["${HOME}/.claude/serper-mcp-server.js"],
      "env": {
        "SERPER_API_KEY": "${SERPER_API_KEY}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Tavily MCP Server (Official)

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "tavily": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@tavily/mcp-server"],
      "env": {
        "TAVILY_API_KEY": "${TAVILY_API_KEY}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

